-- Kingdom Sells Mauritius Hotel to Outrigger for $40 Million
-- B y   D e e m a   A l m a s h a b i
-- 2013-06-01T09:27:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-01/kingdom-sells-movenpick-mauritius-to-outrigger-for-40-million.html
Kingdom Hotel Investments sold the
Movenpick Resort & Spa in Mauritius, located in the  Indian
Ocean , for 150 million riyals ($40 million) to Hawaii-based
Outrigger Hotels and Resorts.  The subsidiary of  Kingdom Holding Co. (KINGDOM)  completed the
transaction on May 29, it said in a  statement  to the Saudi stock
market today.  Kingdom Holding focuses on acquiring stakes in high-value
hotels and real estate in the Middle East and internationally.
Its Kingdom Hotel unit owns stakes in 20 resorts and hotels in
15 countries, with two more hotels under constructions,
according to Kingdom Holding’s  website .  The Raffles Seychelles Resort and Residence, in which
Kingdom Hotel holds a 38 percent stake and which is valued at
$137 million and managed by Fairmont, opened on May 27,
according to Kingdom Holding. The event was attended by  Prince
Alwaleed bin Talal , the world’s 17th-richest person according to
the Bloomberg Billionaires Index.  To contact the reporter on this story:
